# Edge Visual Asset Production

## Available MCP Tools

Two MCP servers are configured in `.cursor/mcp.json` for visual asset production:

- **LogoLoom** (`logoloom`): Generate complete brand kits — logo SVG, favicon, OG image, all PNG sizes. Use for brand identity assets (logo, favicon, social share image).
- **QuiverAI** (`quiverai`): Generate SVG icons and illustrations from text prompts, vectorize raster images, animate existing SVGs. Use for custom icons and any SVG asset generation.

## Available Skills

Three project skills provide detailed production instructions:

- **visual-assets**: Full asset inventory, brand context, icon prompts, and tool-to-asset mapping. Read this first when producing any visual asset.
- **visual-production**: Orchestrates the production workflow in the correct phase order. Use when starting a visual asset production session.
- **dashmotion**: Generates animated data-flow diagrams as self-contained HTML/SVG files. Use for the signature "Chart → Edge → Research/AI" animation and "How It Works" step flow.

## Brand Design Tokens (Source of Truth)

All visual assets must use these tokens from `docs/foundation/design-system.md`:

- Background: `#0A0B0E` | Surface: `#12131A` | Border: `#1E2030`
- Accent: `#00FF88` (use sparingly — CTAs and highlights only)
- Text: `#E8E9ED` primary, `#8B8FA3` secondary, `#5A5E73` muted
- Display font: Space Grotesk | Body font: DM Sans
- Aesthetic: Minimalist & Refined (Dark Finance)

## When to Use Which Tool

| Asset Type | Tool |
|---|---|
| Logo, favicon, OG image | LogoLoom MCP |
| Custom SVG icons | QuiverAI MCP |
| Animated flow diagrams | Dashmotion skill |
| Product UI mockups | Superdesign (web, not MCP) |
| Background effects, scroll animations, hover states | Code (CSS/JS) |
| Particle effects | tsParticles library |
| Cinematic scroll reveals | Framer Motion |
| Third-party logos | `simple-icons` npm package |

## Production Workflow

Always follow the phase order in the `visual-production` skill:
1. Brand identity (LogoLoom) → 2. Icons (QuiverAI) → 3. Mockup (Superdesign) → 4. Animations (Dashmotion) → 5. Verify
